Text: The Starling Five launched from Orbit Station Helios just after sunrise, though sunrise was more a concept than a view at that altitude.
Still, the crew cheered as the engines burned the edge of the world into a band of shimmering gold.
Captain Mira Solène floated weightlessly in the command deck, grinning at her four teammates. “All right, team,” she said. “First deep-range survey mission.
Let’s make history.” The crew—Samir, Jin, Aleya, and Rowan—shouted back in overlapping excitement.
For them, this wasn’t just a mission; it was the realization of childhood dreams.
They’d trained together for years, bonded through simulations and sleepless nights and shared ambitions.
